How to import:

mongoimport export.json -d articles -c articles --drop

First, start with the mongoimport program name.
Next, specify the path to the books.json data file. In this example, it is export.json.
Third, use -d articles to specify the target database, which is articles in this example.
Fourth, use -c articles to specify the target collection, which is articles in this case.
Finally, use the --drop flag to drop the collection if it exists before importing the data
